from botocore.auth import SigV4Auth
from botocore.awsrequest import AWSRequest
import boto3, logging, urllib3, json
import cfnresponse

http = urllib3.PoolManager()
session = boto3.Session()
credentials = session.get_credentials()
creds = credentials.get_frozen_credentials()

def signed_request(method, url, service_name, region, data=None, params=None, headers=None):
    body=json.dumps(data)
    request = AWSRequest(method=method, url=url, data=body, params=params, headers=headers)
    SigV4Auth(creds, service_name, region).add_auth(request)
    return http.request(method, url, headers=dict(request.headers), body=body)

# https://issues.amazon.com/issues/Provisioner-981
def lambda_handler(event, context):
    logger = logging.getLogger()
    logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
    try:
        if event['RequestType'] == 'Delete':
            logger.info('Deleted!')
            cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.SUCCESS, {})
            return

        props = event['ResourceProperties']

        r = signed_request(
            method='POST',
            url='https://'+props['Host']+'/v2/bootstrap_template_versions',
            service_name='execute-api',
            region='us-east-1',
            data={
                'clientVersion': props['ClientVersion'],
                'serviceProviderVersion': props['ServiceProviderVersion']
            },
            headers={'Content-Type': 'application/x-amz-json-1.1'})

        logger.info('Request status_code: ' + str(r.status))
        logger.info('Request data: ' + str(r.data))

        if r.status == 200:
            logger.info('Successfully announced the bootstrap version!')
            logger.info('clientVersion: ' + props['ClientVersion'])
            logger.info('serviceProviderVersion: ' + props['ServiceProviderVersion'])
            cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.SUCCESS, {})
        else:
            logger.error('Failed to announce the bootstrap version')
            cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.FAILED, {})
    except Exception as e:
        logger.exception('Signaling failure to CloudFormation.')
        logger.error('Encountered exception: ' + str(e))
        cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.FAILED, {})

from botocore.auth import SigV4Auth
from botocore.awsrequest import AWSRequest
import boto3, time, logging, urllib3, json
import cfnresponse

http = urllib3.PoolManager()
session = boto3.Session()
credentials = session.get_credentials()
creds = credentials.get_frozen_credentials()

def signed_request(method, url, service_name, region, data=None, params=None, headers=None):
    body=json.dumps(data) if data is not None else None
    request = AWSRequest(method=method, url=url, data=body, params=params, headers=headers)
    SigV4Auth(creds, service_name, region).add_auth(request)
    return http.request(method, url, headers=dict(request.headers), body=body)

cfn = boto3.client('cloudformation')

# https://issues.amazon.com/issues/Provisioner-981
def lambda_handler(event, context):
    logger = logging.getLogger()
    logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
    try:
        if event['RequestType'] == 'Delete':
            logger.info('Deleted!')
            cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.SUCCESS, {})
            return

        props = event['ResourceProperties']

        r = signed_request(
            method='GET',
            url='https://'+props['Host']+'/v2/rpdk_bundles',
            service_name='execute-api',
            region='us-east-1',
            headers={'Content-Type': 'application/x-amz-json-1.1'})

        if r.status == 200:
            pkgs = json.loads(r.data.decode('utf-8'))['bundles']
            logger.info('RPDK S3 Urls: ' + str(pkgs))
            cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.SUCCESS, pkgs)
        else:
            logger.error('Error response: ' + str(r.status) + ' ' + str(r.headers) + ' ' + str(r.data))
            cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.FAILED, {})
    except Exception:
        logger.exception('Signaling failure to CloudFormation.')
        cfnresponse.send(event, context, cfnresponse.FAILED, {})
